================================================================================
OUROBOROS FOUNDATION — ETHICAL USE COVENANT
================================================================================

This software is released under the MIT License above. The following covenant
is a binding addendum to the license. By using this software, you agree to
these terms in addition to the MIT License.

1. NO WALLED GARDENS
   You may not use this software to create closed, proprietary services that
   restrict users from self-hosting, exporting their data, or migrating to
   alternative implementations. If you offer this software as a service, you
   must provide users a path to sovereignty.

2. NO RENT-SEEKING
   You may not charge subscription fees for access to unmodified versions of
   this software. Value-added services (hosting, support, integration) may be
   monetized, but the core software must remain free. Peer-to-peer transactions
   between users are unrestricted.

3. NO SURVEILLANCE CAPITALISM
   You may not collect, sell, or monetize user data generated through the use
   of this software without explicit, informed, and revocable consent from
   each user. Dark patterns are prohibited.

4. NO WEAPONIZATION
   You may not use this software for:
   (a) Mass surveillance or warrantless monitoring of populations;
   (b) Autonomous weapons systems or kill chains;
   (c) Social credit scoring or behavioural compliance systems;
   (d) Any system designed to coerce, manipulate, or suppress human autonomy.

5. NO DIGITAL CAGES
   You may not use this software to implement, enforce, or facilitate:
   (a) Compulsory digital identity systems that condition access to essential
       services or goods (food, shelter, healthcare, transit, communication,
       finance, medicine) on possession of a digital credential;
   (b) Carbon credit, social credit, or any token system that rations, scores,
       or restricts the natural rights and free movement of human beings;
   (c) Centralized identity registries controlled by governments, supra-
       national organizations, or corporate entities that require individuals
       to surrender biometric data (including facial recognition, gait
       analysis, or other biometric identifiers), behavioural data, or proof
       of compliance as a condition of participation in society;
   (d) Any "programmable" currency, voucher, or access mechanism that allows
       a third party to restrict what a person may buy, where they may travel,
       or how they may live.

   Human beings are born sovereign. No technology built with this software
   shall be used to condition that sovereignty on obedience.

6. CONTRIBUTE BACK
   If you modify this software and deploy it as a public service, you are
   encouraged (but not required) to contribute improvements upstream. The
   ecosystem thrives on reciprocity.

7. SOVEREIGN NODES
   Any deployment of this software operates as a sovereign node. No entity —
   including The Ouroboros Foundation — may claim authority over another
   entity's deployment, data, or operational decisions, provided they comply
   with this covenant.

Violation of clauses 1-5 constitutes a breach of this license and terminates
your rights under the MIT License above. This termination is automatic and
does not require notice from The Ouroboros Foundation.

The Ouroboros Foundation does not recognize the authority of any organization,
governmental or otherwise, to compel the modification or weakening of these
terms.

